@jreback 
The only difference is that `DataFrame.set_index` *also* takes column keys. But it's completely usable (on master) to pass arrays, list of arrays, or even a mix of arrays and column keys into `keys` (which is confusing too...).

So effectively, `DataFrame.set_index` has `arrays_or_keys` and `Series.set_index` only has `arrays`. The other kwargs (`append`, `inplace`, `verify_integrity`) make sense for both as well.

@jreback @TomAugspurger 
So, do you want me to implement `Series.set_index` separately (which would be duplicating code somewhat), or stay with a changed signature compared to `NDFrame`?

Personally, I don't see why the signatures can't be different - Series and DataFrame *are* different beasts on many levels, so why shouldn't their methods reflect that?
